  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Purpose: To evaluate if lifestyle intervention (diet and exercise) can reduce maternal weight
      gain, the incidence of pregnancy complications and minimize the number of macrosomic infants.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Obese pregnant women with a BMI&gt;30 are randomized to Diet + Exercise, Exercise or control
      (1:1:1) in order to reduce maternal weight gain to less than 5 kg during pregnancy.

      The effect on the children of mothers in this study is evaluated in the study: Is it possible
      to reduce the Number of Macrosomic Infants With Abundant Fat Tissue by Lifestyle Intervention
      during Pregnancy (NCT01235676)
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
